---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { href } from '../../i18n/ui';

const email = 'raphael@plumservices.co';
const updated = 'July 3, 2026';
---

<Base
  lang="en"
  routeKey="terms"
  title="Terms of use — Sereno"
  description="Sereno's terms, written to be read: a free service, your data stays yours, no financial advice."
>
  <article class="section">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <h1>Terms of use</h1>
      <p>Last updated: {updated}</p>
      <p class="notice" lang="fr">
        Version informative — la <a href="/cgu">version française</a> fait foi.
        <span lang="en">(Informative translation — the French version prevails.)</span>
      </p>
      <p>
        These terms are written to be read. They govern the use of the Sereno
        application and website.
      </p>

      <h2>1. The service</h2>
      <p>
        Sereno is a manual-entry personal budgeting application. It works
        without an account (data stored locally on your device) and offers an
        optional free account for syncing across devices.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Free of charge</h2>
      <p>
        The service is currently free, with no ads and no commercial use of
        your data. If a paid tier ever appears, it will be announced clearly in
        advance and will not retroactively affect the free features you already
        use for your existing data.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Your account</h2>
      <p>
        You are responsible for keeping your credentials confidential. Let us
        know promptly about any unauthorized use of your account. The minimum
        age for using the service with an account is 15.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Your data</h2>
      <p>
        The data you enter belongs to you, entirely. You can export it at any
        time (full backup, CSV export) and request the deletion of your account
        and all its data (see the <a href={href('en', 'privacy')}>privacy policy</a>).
      </p>

      <h2>5. Not financial advice</h2>
      <p>
        Sereno displays totals, breakdowns and projections computed from what
        you enter. These are readability tools,
        <strong>not financial, tax or investment advice</strong>. Your
        decisions remain your own.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>
        You agree not to attempt to compromise the service: no unauthorized
        access to other users' data, no deliberate overloading of the
        infrastructure, no unlawful use.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Availability and changes</h2>
      <p>
        Sereno is an independent project provided “as is”. We do our best to
        keep the service reliable and available, without being able to
        guarantee it 100%. Features may evolve; in the event of a major change
        or discontinuation of the sync service, reasonable notice will be given
        along with the means to export your data. Local mode depends on no
        server at all.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the extent permitted by law, the publisher cannot be held liable for
        indirect damages resulting from the use of the service, including local
        data loss — think about backups. Nothing in these terms excludes
        liability for gross negligence or willful misconduct.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by French law. In the event of a dispute, an
        amicable solution will be sought first; failing that, the French courts
        have jurisdiction.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For any question about these terms:
        <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
